Mike,

On November 20, 2006 12:57 PM you wrote:
> ...
> You are asking NAG and the other owners of Aldor to do you a
> favour, which will take time and effort.  Do you really expect
> us to release Aldor as open source if you try and force our hand
> with illegal actions?

No, of course I really don't have any way of forcing anyone's "hand"
even if I were to make the rash move to distribute Aldor source code.
The legitimit owners of Aldor could certainly assert their rights no
matter what action I take. The best I can hope to do is to make it
clear how important I think this issue is.

Nor do I think of this as asking for a personal favor since I
probably have less intellectual investment and certainly less
financial investment in Axiom than many other people. I do however
expect that any rational person with the stated motivations would
have resolved these licensing issues long ago. Resolution is in
everyone's interest and open source licensing is clearly the best
option. By now this has been proven in many different situations.
Continued delay is harmful (maybe even fatal) to both Aldor and
Axiom.

> 
> > > I understand your frustration at the slow progress on this,
> > 
> > Is "slow progress" the same thing as "no progress"? ;)
